      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a strong reaction, but the audit specifically pointed out that your current logic relies heavily on stereotypical profiles to hit our numbers. If we move to EquityCore, we're looking for actual depth and potential, not just checking boxes based on race or background. Why do you think your current method is better than a system that looks for real merit?",
